cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computational complexity and hardness of approximation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of graph theory and reductions also suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of jigsaw puzzles and edge-matching puzzles suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
